valuating serialization options**\\n\\nI'm considering enabling resolveObject in the custom input stream and mapping the wrapper back to byte[]. This approach supports Java serialization using the API, not reflection. I wonder if it feels a bit unnatural. Public Java serialization customization might be altered, but I think that testing the serialized stream could be more about infrastructure than the library itself. Still, it verifies the restoration when it reaches the call site. The library expects byte[], and resolveObject can indeed return that before casting.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Java serialization**\\n\\nI'm exploring the Java serialization process for BCBIKEPrivateKey. The defaultWriteObject method has no non-transient fields aside from serialVersionUID, and it looks like getEncoded returns a byte array. I need to ensure I'm not replacing the root with BCBIKE. During deserialization, I’ll check if ObjectInputStream.readObject in BCBIKEPrivateKey’s readObject method retrieves the object after resolveObject is called. The docs say resolveObject is invoked before returning from readObject, if that's enabled, which is good to remember!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering serialization options**\\n\\nI'm thinking about wrapper serialization and I see that there's no byte array involved, which is good. I might need to use Base64 for encoding. It seems like I have to consider that I'm using Java 8 while the project JDK is set to 21, but it looks like the library supports versions from JDK 15 to 18. I should note that tests can utilize Base64 in Java 8. Alright, let’s keep going!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_kzrKElYg3PqZAbzHIuItx6cd|fc_08c833dab7df8c7b016a260f9326408197839dbfaeebd5ac48", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15to18/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15to18/BCBIKEPrivateKeyTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\n\nimport org.bouncycastle.pqc.crypto.bike.BIKEParameters;\n", "newText": "import java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\nimport java.io.Serializable;\nimport java.util.Base64;\n\nimport org.bouncycastle.pqc.crypto.bike.BIKEParameters;\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static byte[] serialize(BCBIKEPrivateKey privateKey) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream byteOutputStream = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ObjectOutputStream objectOutputStream = new ObjectOutputStream(byteOutputStream)) {\n            objectOutputStream.writeObject(privateKey);\n        }\n        return byteOutputStream.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static BCBIKEPrivateKey deserialize(byte[] serialized) throws Exception {\n        try (ObjectInputStream objectInputStream = new ObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(serialized))) {\n            return (BCBIKEPrivateKey)objectInputStream.readObject();\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static byte[] serialize(BCBIKEPrivateKey privateKey) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream byteOutputStream = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ObjectOutputStream objectOutputStream = new EncodedPrivateKeyReplacingObjectOutputStream(byteOutputStream)) {\n            objectOutputStream.writeObject(privateKey);\n        }\n        return byteOutputStream.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static BCBIKEPrivateKey deserialize(byte[] serialized) throws Exception {\n        try (ObjectInputStream objectInputStream = new EncodedPrivateKeyResolvingObjectInputStream(\n                new ByteArrayInputStream(serialized))) {\n            return (BCBIKEPrivateKey)objectInputStream.readObject();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class EncodedPrivateKeyReplacingObjectOutputStream extends ObjectOutputStream {\n        private EncodedPrivateKeyReplacingObjectOutputStream(ByteArrayOutputStream outputStream) throws IOException {\n            super(outputStream);\n            enableReplaceObject(true);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Object replaceObject(Object object) throws IOException {\n            if (object instanceof byte[]) {\n                return new EncodedPrivateKey((byte[])object);\n            }\n            return super.replaceObject(object);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class EncodedPrivateKeyResolvingObjectInputStream extends ObjectInputStream {\n        private EncodedPrivateKeyResolvingObjectInputStream(ByteArrayInputStream inputStream) throws IOException {\n            super(inputStream);\n            enableResolveObject(true);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Object resolveObject(Object object) throws IOException {\n            if (object instanceof EncodedPrivateKey) {\n                return ((EncodedPrivateKey)object).toByteArray();\n            }\n            return super.resolveObject(object);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class EncodedPrivateKey implements Serializable {\n        private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n\n        private final String encodedBase64;\n\n        private EncodedPrivateKey(byte[] encoded) {\n            this.encodedBase64 = Base64.getEncoder().encodeToString(encoded);\n        }\n\n        private byte[] toByteArray() {\n            return Base64.getDecoder().decode(encodedBase64);\n        }\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1529, "output": 2871, "cacheRead": 35840, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40240, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780879199268, "responseId": "resp_08c833dab7df8c7b016a260f5ff2388197b4654b8cdb851d11"}}
