[assistant] Refined `BCBIKEPrivateKeyTest` to make the active `BCBIKEPrivateKey.writeObject` / `readObject` dynamic-access sites more observable.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated file:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - `tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15to18/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15to18/BCBIKEPrivateKeyTest.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] What changed:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - The test still serializes/deserializes `BCBIKEPrivateKey` through normal Java serialization.
[assistant] - Added custom public-API `ObjectOutputStream` / `ObjectInputStream` subclasses using object replacement/resolution so the encoded private key object written from `BCBIKEPrivateKey.writeObject` is represented as a serializable test helper object and resolved back to `byte[]` before `BCBIKEPrivateKey.readObject` consumes it.
[assistant] - This keeps the test focused on the active class and still verifies the restored key preserves algorithm, format, parameter spec, encoding, equality, and hash code.
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not compile or run tests, per workflow instructions.
