coded) {\n            this.encodedBase64 = Base64.getEncoder().encodeToString(encoded);\n        }\n\n        private byte[] toByteArray() {\n            return Base64.getDecoder().decode(encodedBase64);\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static final class EncodedPrivateKeyReplacingObjectOutputStream extends ObjectOutputStream {\n        private boolean replacedEncodedKey;\n\n        private EncodedPrivateKeyReplacingObjectOutputStream(ByteArrayOutputStream outputStream)\n                throws IOException {\n            super(outputStream);\n            enableReplaceObject(true);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Object replaceObject(Object object) throws IOException {\n            if (!replacedEncodedKey && object instanceof byte[]) {\n                replacedEncodedKey = true;\n                return new BCBIKEPrivateKey(PrivateKeyInfo.getInstance((byte[])object));\n            }\n            return super.replaceObject(object);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class EncodedPrivateKeyResolvingObjectInputStream extends ObjectInputStream {\n        private boolean resolvedNestedKey;\n\n        private EncodedPrivateKeyResolvingObjectInputStream(ByteArrayInputStream inputStream)\n                throws IOException {\n            super(inputStream);\n            enableResolveObject(true);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Object resolveObject(Object object) throws IOException {\n            if (!resolvedNestedKey && object instanceof BCBIKEPrivateKey) {\n                resolvedNestedKey = true;\n                return ((BCBIKEPrivateKey)object).getEncoded();\n            }\n            return super.resolveObject(object);\n        }\n    }\n"}]}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating API implementation**\n\nI’m looking at the rules for using the public API, specifically the ObjectOutputStream’s replaceObject, which seems to be categorized as public/protected. That could be fine, but I need to consider how it alters the actual payload type and if it’s supported. The BCBIKEPrivateKey expects a byte[] from in.readObject, so I want to ensure that works correctly. I might just simplify things by testing Java serialization of a Holder class in org_bouncycastle instead. Also, I’ll replace the previous EncodedPrivateKey helper with a nested BCBIKEPrivateKey, removing the Base64/Serializable aspects and switching to PrivateKeyInfo. It's time to edit!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_08c833dab7df8c7b016a261062c58081978547f8bdf33a067e\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJhB16CrP0uCvVsGOn3VvpkaU3ojlRxaGUtjhFimqzMTv_yYL55VydrcPLUujf8kxJ0l0BubWLdyw4GrMIKexb8swkfb71lH2uTFkbT4_OI7mQ8ItxY0ZfN28agJ7WmOdJyrIIgW-RWikYCq9UO1SN81SMV5itqb7LlWezJBuq3mJ2ofxw8aOaS7vJRaChy4oG3swUopswhJRJkDvtHHfAKo2DdsEDwok43TMs2TrhYByVuw6DjeKyVxb48Xj-0q83wYr9SIVlCrEy7AdIp87KrSqt5ZpIDSa4QjDqjAKrDEyKrLdCpQo0bCNj9oFr05WwRERqOjx4Bi4Frlt9RJ8IURXXyOZGYMQvXctproFOFqSpMKHcec3p8nW94gKO_JnWD52ettnXI4eEqsHea7ymdmYhLqHcTi_MwX6JassCa2axOJ-LkZ7_b15qx80c0x8Lmv0LAyxn4eX6qq7js_F67gsd6i4HWtseCEY3PRUWm7wRr0qfhhOPUcGmK8h8AyORuGE_SlRTi2ok2NB2hL9UlZ2SOnx57V7BJ5rDEvfOj8vh5i4ekTPJ0p14GJ2NxLOXlqOUahGbirgezOoih5Yr8RogDshlvx96cddIjmsjcac0Ua7cu3dD64YlWzGTXD-A_WMrNgJydk2qDBLNkDxL-1To8iE0mQbjUWIP1lCmEV_RAaT9dUE9v5h_QVWfGWPl0Q-tee4rT7azywfFM3PTWkVvNrQf_5-kJGgWcBi2fvqvaSOGdk7jsRTLOief-IbZ7dotK-6GjgCGQf-ENAJo67mh6tB4yDwU4EAEKBBOEEzv90TkclDxNgJMRhlrsMI727blKaYrQu4oiOy6nOMJaTN8eqs7wOWW6rQ78OkGI0aPGghWCYuaMGDhrx8-r39l-FxCklxidDMlIZrWgDeFTYt7KsGVWPO4j59g6IVgUl_MyCcElF1V8irRUxXaD-a60_HgBK7Mb--0oGVyY3f4YwxtxhCgppKGEsJRXi_16fA45iY39ilUd7YvCjZoIPjw4bQJbnViXtHMC7JvI5wbW