 fine, but I need to consider how it alters the actual payload type and if it’s supported. The BCBIKEPrivateKey expects a byte[] from in.readObject, so I want to ensure that works correctly. I might just simplify things by testing Java serialization of a Holder class in org_bouncycastle instead. Also, I’ll replace the previous EncodedPrivateKey helper with a nested BCBIKEPrivateKey, removing the Base64/Serializable aspects and switching to PrivateKeyInfo. It's time to edit!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_PrtYB59GAAtMflGSbTRKccii|fc_08c833dab7df8c7b016a2610751cbc8197b6f48c47a2af1d06", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15to18/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15to18/BCBIKEPrivateKeyTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.Serializable;\nimport java.util.Base64;\n\nimport org.bouncycastle.pqc.crypto.bike.BIKEParameters;\n", "newText": "\nimport org.bouncycastle.asn1.pkcs.PrivateKeyInfo;\nimport org.bouncycastle.pqc.crypto.bike.BIKEParameters;\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static final class EncodedPrivateKeyReplacingObjectOutputStream extends ObjectOutputStream {\n        private EncodedPrivateKeyReplacingObjectOutputStream(ByteArrayOutputStream outputStream)\n                throws IOException {\n            super(outputStream);\n            enableReplaceObject(true);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Object replaceObject(Object object) throws IOException {\n            if (object instanceof byte[]) {\n                return new EncodedPrivateKey((byte[])object);\n            }\n            return super.replaceObject(object);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class EncodedPrivateKeyResolvingObjectInputStream extends ObjectInputStream {\n        private EncodedPrivateKeyResolvingObjectInputStream(ByteArrayInputStream inputStream)\n                throws IOException {\n            super(inputStream);\n            enableResolveObject(true);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Object resolveObject(Object object) throws IOException {\n            if (object instanceof EncodedPrivateKey) {\n                return ((EncodedPrivateKey)object).toByteArray();\n            }\n            return super.resolveObject(object);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class EncodedPrivateKey implements Serializable {\n        private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n\n        private final String encodedBase64;\n\n        private EncodedPrivateKey(byte[] encoded) {\n            this.encodedBase64 = Base64.getEncoder().encodeToString(encoded);\n        }\n\n        private byte[] toByteArray() {\n            return Base64.getDecoder().decode(encodedBase64);\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static final class EncodedPrivateKeyReplacingObjectOutputStream extends ObjectOutputStream {\n        private boolean replacedEncodedKey;\n\n        private EncodedPrivateKeyReplacingObjectOutputStream(ByteArrayOutputStream outputStream)\n                throws IOException {\n            super(outputStream);\n            enableReplaceObject(true);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Object replaceObject(Object object) throws IOException {\n            if (!replacedEncodedKey && object instanceof byte[]) {\n                replacedEncodedKey = true;\n                return new BCBIKEPrivateKey(PrivateKeyInfo.getInstance((byte[])object));\n            }\n            return super.replaceObject(object);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class EncodedPrivateKeyResolvingObjectInputStream extends ObjectInputStream {\n        private boolean resolvedNestedKey;\n\n        private EncodedPrivateKeyResolvingObjectInputStream(ByteArrayInputStream inputStream)\n                throws IOException {\n            super(inputStream);\n            enableResolveObject(true);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Object resolveObject(Object object) throws IOException {\n            if (!resolvedNestedKey && object instanceof BCBIKEPrivateKey) {\n                resolvedNestedKey = true;\n                return ((BCBIKEPrivateKey)object).getEncoded();\n            }\n            return super.resolveObject(object);\n        }\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 550, "output": 1612, "cacheRead": 50176, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 52338, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780879457542, "responseId": "resp_08c833dab7df8c7b016a26106225608197b6d3c2b0ff767793"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_PrtYB59GAAtMflGSbTRKccii|fc_08c833dab7df8c7b016a2610751cbc8197b6f48c47a2af1d06", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 2 block(s) in tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15to18/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15to18/BCBIKEPrivateKeyTest.java."}], "details": {"diff": "     ...\n  13 import java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\n  14 import java.io.IOException;\n  15 import java.io.ObjectInputStream;\n  16 import java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\n- 17 import java.io.Serializable;\n- 18 import java.util.Base64;\n  19 \n+ 18 import org.bouncycastle.asn1.pkcs.PrivateKeyInfo;\n  20 import org.bouncycastle.pqc.crypto.bike.BIKEParameters;\n  21 import org.bouncycastle.pqc.crypto.bike.BIKEPrivateKeyParameters;\n  22 import org.bouncycastle.pqc.jcajce.provider.bike.BCBIKEPrivateKey;\n  23 import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n     ...\n  71         }\n  72     }\n  73 \n  74     private static final class EncodedPrivateKeyReplacingObjectOutputStream extends ObjectOutputStream {\n+ 74         private boolean replacedEncodedKey;\n+ 75 \n  75         private EncodedPrivateKeyReplacingObjectOutputStream(ByteArrayOutputStream outputStream)\n  76                 throws IOException {\n  77             super(outputStream);\n  78             enableReplaceObject(true);\n  79 